  "body_html": "<p>I spend lots of time on math, exercise, hanging out with loved ones, and exploring interesting things. </p><div class=\"captioned-image-container\"><figure><a class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!ylNJ!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a857ece-77ae-4485-820e-4c43ab94321d_375x334.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\"><div class=\"image2-inset\"><picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!ylNJ!,w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a857ece-77ae-4485-820e-4c43ab94321d_375x334.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!ylNJ!,w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a857ece-77ae-4485-820e-4c43ab94321d_375x334.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!ylNJ!,w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a857ece-77ae-4485-820e-4c43ab94321d_375x334.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!ylNJ!,w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a857ece-77ae-4485-820e-4c43ab94321d_375x334.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!ylNJ!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a857ece-77ae-4485-820e-4c43ab94321d_375x334.png\" width=\"375\" height=\"334\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/7a857ece-77ae-4485-820e-4c43ab94321d_375x334.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:334,&quot;width&quot;:375,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:229623,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://chillphysicsenjoyer.substack.com/i/171602250?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a857ece-77ae-4485-820e-4c43ab94321d_375x334.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" class=\"sizing-normal\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!ylNJ!,w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a857ece-77ae-4485-820e-4c43ab94321d_375x334.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!ylNJ!,w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a857ece-77ae-4485-820e-4c43ab94321d_375x334.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!ylNJ!,w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a857ece-77ae-4485-820e-4c43ab94321d_375x334.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!ylNJ!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a857ece-77ae-4485-820e-4c43ab94321d_375x334.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><div class=\"image-link-expand\"><div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\"><button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\"><svg role=\"img\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><g><title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path></g></svg></button><button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\"><polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line></svg></button></div></div></div></a></figure></div><p>But sometimes, I need to do something concrete. These things are \u2018tasks\u2019 in my to-do list. Examples includes coding, writing, literature review, planning, emails, workshops, personal finance, mathematical derivations and more! </p><p>I\u2019ve realised that any task I get can be shrunk to a twenty minute job. This motivates myself to do things a lot.</p><p>Here\u2019s how. </p><div><hr></div><p>Tasks seek to accomplish goals. So when I get a task, I think of the minimal of goals associated with it. </p><p>I then list different tasks that achieve the <strong>same set of goals</strong>. Then, I remove things from those tasks even more, such that the goals are still achieved to the same order of magnitude. If the goal involves numbers, like \u2018make 100 things\u2019 or \u2018invite 20 people\u2019, I divide it by 10 and see if it really makes a difference. </p><p>Most of the time, cutting specs like this doesn\u2019t affect the end goals at all. And at the end of this, I\u2019ve reduced a big task to a twenty minute job. </p><p>Here\u2019s an example.</p><p>Last week, I had to run a workshop on formalising physics. On the surface, this meant making a 10 pages long slide show, writing a script, making invites, writing example code, and so on. A big task! It could probably take a day! I aimed for 30 people to come. </p><p>But what was the goal? Well, I thought about what the task was trying to achieve. At its core, it was to make people excited about contribute to the Phys LEAN projects, and make people aware of it. </p><p>For my workshop, I realised that I could just have one title slide, and spend most of the time showing a screen share of me playing a LEAN game. And then just show the website of cool projects pages on the screen share too. I also realised that 10 people would be fine, so just threw a link on the discord the week before. </p><p>Job done!<br></p>",
